l good points.<br>
<br>
It's a very realistic view of a paladin/sk fight, couple of minor tweaks - though i am more of an oldschool dualer but will include some new tricks to.<br>
<br>
lv9-49 <br>
I would wager the shadowknight winining every fight.<br>
ATK, STR debuffs really hamper the paladins DPS by a lot at those lvs, most people wont have high Strength or Attack.. and a simple strength buff can encumber the unaware paladin easy (worse before lv30 armor as most armor/wepons are heavy) and an encumbered paladin is very easy to hit and doesnt hurt you much.<br>
<br>
50+ is when it gets fun, most have very good selection of Resist armors, Tanking armors, wepon selections and utility items.<br>
<br>
Shadowknight spell damage is misleading, Dots/taps in PvP are Very mana in-efficent..... healing is the same efficency if in PvP or out of PvP.<br>
     If i waste all my mana doing Dots - then i wont have mana to lifetap, then when the end of a fight comes i watch the paladin Lay hands or root and back out ot heal to full with me left at 30% hit points and 10% mana.<br>
<br>
Ac on paladin and shadowknight is equal, bear in mind we have AC buffs/Debuffs - that will debuff you and give to us.. these debuffs are configurable so give or take a point or two we are above/under paladin AC... so fairly equal there.<br>
<br>
We can dispell yours buffs and you ours, however the shadowknight has a lot of reasonably low cost buffs that he can junk on him self and debuff you on a 1.5 second cast. So debuffing an shadowknight is a loosing battle - they will just laughat you, while a shadowknight will happily dispell your buff knowing you cant recast it.<br>
<br>
Pets, once feared are not an issue, flash of light/spook undead, often pets go wierd in duals anyway - but can be quite good.<br>
<br>
About the best way to beat a paladin is keep stunning him as he trys to heal - sometimes you can get scared paladins to chain heal and keep getting interupted, wich is when they blow there mana trying to out distance you - meaning you can get lots and lots of free damage.<br>
<br>
Lifetaps do damage also but at 2/3rd there rate so really use them to heal not do damage.<br>
<br>
Saying all this i would love to fight an AAed up paladin at 60 (once i get a bucket load of AA of course) it would be interesting to see if me and my pet if it survives can do enough damage to kill a paladin with all there extreemly low cast time heals....... the new heals are so nice i really do think i would have trouble in the fight.... WICH is great, so far paladins have been push overs and only at 50+ do they begin to challenge you.<br>
